OL,3,CLocal elections: How could the West
OL,4,CMidlands change after the 7th May?
OL,6,FThe map below shows the sea of Red and
OL,7,FBlue that currently dominates the West
OL,8,FMidlands' City and Borough councils.
OL,9,FIf the map is not visible on your
OL,10,Fdevice, click here.
OL,12,FMost of the councils were elected in
OL,13,F2024, when Labour was riding high
OL,14,Fbefore the general election, which saw
OL,15,FKeir Starmer win a massive majority in
OL,16,FWestminster.
OL,18,FBirmingham is the only exception, last
OL,19,Fgoing to the polls in 2022 in the wake
OL,20,Fof Partygate.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G2/17
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,373,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1778008271
OL,3,CLocal elections: How could the West
OL,4,CMidlands change after the 7th May?
OL,6,FSince then, Labour's popularity has
OL,7,Fplummeted, and the Tories have failed
OL,8,Fto recover.
OL,10,FThis has left a big gap for other
OL,11,Fparties like Reform UK and the Green
OL,12,FParty, who are both targeting the West
OL,13,FMidlands.
OL,15,FBut aside from Dudley, where Reform UK
OL,16,Flooks to be in poll position, no party
OL,17,Fhas come close to the high vote share
OL,18,Fthat both Labour and the Conservatives
OL,19,Fare used to.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/17
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,373,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1778008271
OL,3,CLocal elections: How could the West
OL,4,CMidlands change after the 7th May?
OL,6,FSo what are the key battles to watch
OL,7,Ffor when the results are declared on
OL,8,Fthe 8th of May?
OL,10,FWalsall Council
OL,12,FUnlike most of the West Midlands,
OL,13,FWalsall has not always had one clear
OL,14,Fpolitical leaning. It's seen most
OL,15,Ftypes of administration from Labour,
OL,16,FTory, to Labour-Lib Dem coalition.
OL,18,FBut for the first time, there could be
OL,19,Fa new group in charge.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/17
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,373,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1778008271
OL,3,CLocal elections: How could the West
OL,4,CMidlands change after the 7th May?
OL,6,FReform UK is six points ahead of the
OL,7,FConservatives in the polls and
OL,8,Fexpected to perform well.
OL,10,FIf they over-perform as they did in
OL,11,Fthe local elections in 2025, they
OL,12,Fcould wrestle power from the
OL,13,FConservatives.
OL,15,FDudley Borough Council
OL,17,FReform UK is likely to do very well in
OL,18,FDudley.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G5/17
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,373,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1778008271
OL,3,CLocal elections: How could the West
OL,4,CMidlands change after the 7th May?
OL,6,FMost polling across the West Midlands
OL,7,Fshows a mixed picture, with no party
OL,8,Fclearly in front.
OL,10,FThat's not true in Dudley.
OL,12,FReform UK have a 21-point poll lead
OL,13,F(41%) on the next most popular party,
OL,14,FLabour (20%).
OL,16,FThis would be bad news for the
OL,17,FConservatives, who are currently
OL,18,Frunning the show, but only a third of
OL,19,Fcouncillors are put up for election.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G6/17
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,373,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1778008271
OL,3,CLocal elections: How could the West
OL,4,CMidlands change after the 7th May?
OL,6,FEven if all of the seats up for grabs
OL,7,Fgo to Reform, they still wouldn't have
OL,8,Fenough for a majority.
OL,10,FThe Tory leader, Kemi Badenoch, has
OL,11,Ftold ITV News Central that she's open
OL,12,Fto working with Reform at the local
OL,13,Flevel, so there is every chance this
OL,14,Fcould be one of the country's first
OL,15,FConservative-Reform coalitions.
OL,17,FSoilhull Metropolitan Borough Council
OL,19,FSolihull is a true-blue council. The
OL,20,FConservatives have never been out of
OL,21,Fpower since their formation in 1973.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G7/17
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,373,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37208
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1778008271
OL,3,CLocal elections: How could the West
OL,4,CMidlands change after the 7th May?
OL,6,FThey survived the local council Tory
OL,7,Fwipeout before the 2024 and 1997
OL,8,Felections.
OL,10,FWhilst the council is no stranger to a
OL,11,Fno overall control result, the
OL,12,FConservatives have had a healthy
OL,13,Fmajority for the last 16 years.
OL,15,FBut even before the recent boost
OL,16,Fthey've seen in the poll in the last
OL,17,Fsix months, the Green Party has been a
OL,18,Fgrowing force in Solihull.
OL,20,FThey've held double-digit council
OL,21,Fseats for the last decade.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G8/17
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,373,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37209
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1778008271
OL,3,CLocal elections: How could the West
OL,4,CMidlands change after the 7th May?
OL,6,FWhilst Reform UK has a big poll lead
OL,7,Fover the Greens, the vote will be
OL,8,Fsplit on the right, which could lead
OL,9,Fthe Greens to make big gains.
OL,11,FIf Reform UK performs above
OL,12,Fexpectations, as they did in the Local
OL,13,Felections in 2025, this could be
OL,14,Fanother Tory mainstay going turquoise,
OL,15,Fbut there is still a chance this could
OL,16,Fbe held up as a surprise win for the
OL,17,FGreens.
OL,19,FCoventry City Council and Sandwell
OL,20,FBorough Council
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G9/17
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,373,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37210
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1778008271
OL,3,CLocal elections: How could the West
OL,4,CMidlands change after the 7th May?
OL,6,FCoventry and Sandwell are Labour
OL,7,Fstrongholds.
OL,9,FIn Coventry, Labour has been in power
OL,10,Ffor 46 years out of the 52-year
OL,11,Fexistence. In Sandwell, Labour's been
OL,12,Feven more dominant. They've run the
OL,13,Fcouncil uninterrupted since 1979.
OL,15,FThroughout the "Winter of Discontent",
OL,16,FMargaret Thatcher's entire
OL,17,Fpremiership, the financial crash and
OL,18,FBrexit, these councils have held firm.
OL,20,FLast time round, Labour won 50% of the
OL,21,Fvote in Coventry and 57% in Sandwell.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G10/17
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,373,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37211
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1778008271
OL,3,CLocal elections: How could the West
OL,4,CMidlands change after the 7th May?
OL,6,FBut this time, that red wall could
OL,7,Fcrack not by one party's overwhelming
OL,8,Fpopularity but instead by losing votes
OL,9,Fon all sides.
OL,11,FRecent polls have Labour and Reform UK
OL,12,Fneck-and-neck in Coventry, and Reform
OL,13,Fslightly ahead in Sandwell.
OL,15,FBut they're also likely to lose votes
OL,16,Fto their left with the Greens surging
OL,17,Fin popularity in both areas.
OL,19,FAs with most of the councils,
OL,20,Fcoalitions will be a big question.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G11/17
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,373,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37212
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1778008271
OL,3,CLocal elections: How could the West
OL,4,CMidlands change after the 7th May?
OL,6,FBoth the Green Party and Labour have
OL,7,Fruled out joining up with Reform UK,
OL,8,Fso if they do perform well, they'll be
OL,9,Flooking to the Tories for a chance to
OL,10,Fget into power.
OL,12,FCould a Green Party Labour coalition
OL,13,Falso be on the cards, or will Labour's
OL,14,Flong history keep them in post?
OL,16,FWolverhampton City Council
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G12/17
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,373,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37213
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1778008271
OL,3,CLocal elections: How could the West
OL,4,CMidlands change after the 7th May?
OL,6,FWolverhampton is Labour's safest
OL,7,Fcouncil in the West Midlands.
OL,8,FUnsurprisingly, it's where Keir
OL,9,FStarmer launched the party's local
OL,10,Felection campaign.
OL,12,FOnly a third of the seats in the
OL,13,Fcouncil are up for grabs. Labour's
OL,14,Fmajority on the council means it would
OL,15,Ftake all of those going to the
OL,16,Fopposing Conservatives to see a shift
OL,17,Fin overall control.
OL,19,FWhilst this election will be
OL,20,Funpredictable, polling makes that seem
OL,21,Funlikely.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G13/17
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,373,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37214
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1778008271
OL,3,CLocal elections: How could the West
OL,4,CMidlands change after the 7th May?
OL,6,FDespite this, Reform UK is still
OL,7,Flikely to do well.
OL,9,FBirmingham City Council
OL,11,FBirmingham is the least predictable of
OL,12,Fany of the elections in the West
OL,13,FMidlands.
OL,15,FThe Tories, Greens, Reform UK, Lib
OL,16,FDems and Independents are all hoping
OL,17,Fto make gains.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G14/17
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,373,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37215
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1778008271
OL,3,CLocal elections: How could the West
OL,4,CMidlands change after the 7th May?
OL,6,FBut the Labour Party isn't going to be
OL,7,Fturfed out without a fight and will
OL,8,Flikely be relying on its historic
OL,9,Fpopularity in the city.
OL,11,FA poll by ITV Central with More In
OL,12,FCommon showed Labour could lose half
OL,13,Fits seats.
OL,15,FThe survey predicted Labour falling
OL,16,Ffrom 65 seats in 2022 to just 32.
OL,17,FReform UK is forecast to make major
OL,18,Fgains, winning 26 seats, pushing the
OL,19,FConservatives into third place with 25
OL,20,Fseats.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G15/17
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,373,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37216
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1778008271
OL,3,CLocal elections: How could the West
OL,4,CMidlands change after the 7th May?
OL,6,FThe Liberal Democrats are expected to
OL,7,Fwin 10 seats and the Greens 7, with
OL,8,FIndependents taking 1.
OL,10,FLike all polls, this is just a
OL,11,Fsnapshot of a moment in time, and
OL,12,Fthere is evidence that Independents,
OL,13,Fspecifically, might have been
OL,14,Funderpriced.
OL,16,FBut it still shows a significant shift
OL,17,Ffrom 2022, when Labour held 65 seats,
OL,18,Fcompared to 22 for the Conservatives,
OL,19,F12 for the Liberal Democrats and just
OL,20,F2 for the Greens.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G16/17
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
